, 1940) nomen dubium
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="nomen dubium" baseAuthorityName="Szilady" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon trizonus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trizonus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon trizonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unclear. The species was described based on two male and two female syntypes labelled &quot;La Calle [el Kala], Algeria&quot; and &quot;Ain Draham, Tunisia&quot;, which were not examined. Originally, the syntypes were located in the Hungarian National Museum in Budapest, but the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
collection was destroyed by a fire in 1956. The description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Szilady, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="34 - 70" refId="B66" refString="Szilady, L, 1940. Ueber Palaearktische Syrphiden. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 33: 34 - 70" title="Ueber Palaearktische Syrphiden." volume="33" year="1940">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Szilády">Szilady</normalizedToken>
(1940)
</bibRefCitation>
is incomplete and based on a few differences from the related species 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. hirsutus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The types of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. trizonus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="trizonus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. trizonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are assumed lost and the description is insufficiently accurate to associate name to one of these species. Currently, two species from the 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. serrulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, to which 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. hirsutus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs, occur in northern Africa, namely 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. bequaerti" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. sophron." pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="sophron.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. sophron.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Therefore, we propose to leave the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="nomen dubium" baseAuthorityName="Szilady" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon trizonus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trizonus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon trizonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Szilády">Szilady</normalizedToken>
, 1940) as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">nomen dubium</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
